{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c2c45df6-4a86-48d3-bf3b-fd6b70d3c52f","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 — here's the modern pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous init here (lightweight setup only)\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // await async resources (DB connections, HTTP clients, etc.)\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup runs after each test\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        // await async teardown\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor injection** of `TestContext` is the modern MSTest v3 approach (replaces the `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern).\n- Use the **constructor** for synchronous, lightweight setup.\n- Use **`[TestInitialize]`** for `async` setup — constructors can't be async.\n- Use **`[TestCleanup]`** for async teardown.\n- For one-time class-level setup, use `[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` (these are static).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c4e691fc-4b6e-4637-b85b-cd947f280bbf","outputTokens":371,"requestId":"A02A:2240A:651A2F3:6DA079B:6A034CDA"},"id":"5baee004-9a93-459f-8b35-568df376a9bd","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:53:06.970Z","parentId":"48aeed68-9f58-4e7e-8a3b-5979628c09e2"}
